title: RAF Cosford conservation work on display
text:
Among them is the Range Safety Launch, RSL, 43ft boat. With four crew members and a top speed of 20 knots, RSL 1667 saw service in the Far East based out of RAF Seletar, Singapore. For more information on events in and around Wolverhampton click here . 
The majority of the conservation work on RSL 1667 has been carried out by museum volunteers. What do you think? Be the first to comment 
Conservation centre manager, Darren Priday said: 
“This is one of only three examples of the type remaining so the significance of this project is huge.” Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
